---
description: TypeScript and Figma widget coding conventions
globs: widget-src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

## TypeScript Style

- Use **strict** TypeScript with explicit types where it improves clarity; avoid `any`.
- Prefer `interface` for data shapes (`TaskItem`, props) and `type` for unions / utility types.
- Keep function signatures small and focused; extract complex logic into `utils/` instead of bloating components.

## Figma Widget Patterns

- Use `figma.widget` primitives (`AutoLayout`, `Text`, `Input`, `SVG`) instead of generic React/DOM APIs.
- For state:
  - Only call `useSyncedState` in the root widget component (`TextToChecklistWidget` in `code.tsx`).
  - Pass state and setters down via props; **do not** introduce additional global or module-level mutable state.
- When interacting with `figma.showUI` / `figma.ui`:
  - Keep message types small and explicit (e.g. `{ type: 'add-tasks', text }`).
  - Handle all `figma.ui.onmessage` branches defensively (null/empty text, unexpected types).

## Tasks & Parsing

- Always operate on `TaskItem` arrays; do not introduce alternative task shapes.
- When adding tasks from text:
  - Call `parseTasks` with the raw string.
  - Append or merge using a deep-copied `tasks` array:
    ```ts
    const newTasks = parseTasks(msg.text);
    setTasks([...tasks, ...newTasks]);
    ```
- If you extend parsing (e.g. new bullet formats, indentation rules), do so inside `parseTasks.ts` and keep it **pure** and testable.

## Components

- `Header`:
  - Renders title, subtitle, and theme toggle only; do not add task mutation logic here.
- `ActionBar`:
  - Owns high-level actions (add items, toggle edit/delete modes, clear/delete completed, export).
  - Avoid embedding parsing or formatting logic that belongs in `utils/`.
- `TaskRow`:
  - Owns checkbox behavior, indent/outdent, text editing, merge-up, and URL chips.
  - When modifying the `tasks` array, follow the deep-copy pattern and keep behavior consistent for parent/child tasks.

## Theming, Colors, Icons

- Always obtain colors and theme values via `getTheme(isDark)` and constants in `widget-src/constants/colors.ts`.
- Always obtain icons via `ICON_*` imports from `widget-src/constants/icons.ts`.
- Do not hardcode hex values or inline SVGs into components; add them to the constants files instead.
